<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-10"><hi rend="italic">August 10,
                                        1900.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Goodnow to immediately forward to Minister
                                Conger the following cipher message:</p>
                            <p>August 10, morning. Receipt of Mr. Conger’s cipher telegram,
                                identical with telegrams of French and other ministers, is
                                acknowledged; his determination not to accept Chinese escort is
                                approved. This determination has been communicated to Chinese
                                Government and their cooperation with relief expedition which
                                captured Yangtsu on August 6 has been urged.</p>
                            <p>Dispatches in cipher should be dated.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>